			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">A power battery, also known as an energy storage device, is an electrochemical device that stores electrical energy in the form of chemical energy and releases it as electrical energy when needed. It consists of one or more electrochemical cells that undergo reversible chemical reactions during charging and discharging cycles. Most EVs today are powered by lithium-ion batteries.</common:generalComment>
